1
00:00:01,070 --> 00:00:12,180
♪

2
00:00:12,180 --> 00:00:15,150
♪ (singing in Japanese) ♪

3
00:00:15,150 --> 00:01:33,160
♪

4
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:44,290
♪

5
00:01:46,050 --> 00:01:53,180
♪

6
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:55,160
Guess it's time to say goodbye.

7
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,080
Kaoru, when you get to Edo

8
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:59,020
please go visit Sherry Baby's.

9
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:00,090
That's my old restaurant.

10
00:02:00,090 --> 00:02:01,050
I've already written

11
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:03,030
to let them know you're coming.

12
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:04,180
Okay, Sherry Baby's.

13
00:02:04,180 --> 00:02:06,020
Thank you, thanks a lot.

14
00:02:06,020 --> 00:02:08,200
You know, that's the
sister restaurant of Lenny's.

15
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,010
I feel so lonely.

16
00:02:10,010 --> 00:02:11,050
It seems like everyone

17
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:12,290
is leaving Kyoto.

18
00:02:12,290 --> 00:02:14,030
Bye, Yoshi.

19
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:15,130
Take care of yourself.

20
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:16,130
Sure.

21
00:02:16,130 --> 00:02:18,020
We won't be gone very long.

22
00:02:18,020 --> 00:02:19,010
We'll find him.

23
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:21,200
And be back real soon.

24
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,070
-Bye.
-See ya.

25
00:02:23,070 --> 00:02:24,030
When you come back

26
00:02:24,030 --> 00:02:25,260
I'll make you some sashimi.

27
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:26,280
Yeah!

28
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,280
Kaoru, wait!

29
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,170
Huh?

30
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:30,160
Don't go yet!

31
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:33,020
We made it, we made it!

32
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:34,040
Hi, everybody!

33
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,140
You got here just in time.

34
00:02:35,140 --> 00:02:36,130
Take care now.

35
00:02:36,130 --> 00:02:37,170
I'm really gonna miss you all.

36
00:02:37,170 --> 00:02:38,180
Well, I'm glad
to see the patient

37
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:40,130
is finally well
enough to travel.

38
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:41,140
Good luck, Kaoru!

39
00:02:41,140 --> 00:02:42,230
So long, Kaoru!

40
00:02:42,230 --> 00:02:43,230
Say hi to all the ladies

41
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:44,290
in Edo for me.

42
00:02:44,290 --> 00:02:46,190
Thank you again
for all your help!

43
00:02:46,190 --> 00:02:47,270
Huh?

44
00:02:47,270 --> 00:02:49,060
If it weren't for you
and all the support

45
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:50,220
and encouragement you gave me

46
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:51,250
I don't know what I would have--

47
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:53,140
Well, I'm glad you
finally realized

48
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:55,210
all the appreciation I deserve.

49
00:02:55,210 --> 00:02:57,050
Now get going, you silly fool,

50
00:02:57,050 --> 00:02:59,000
before that riverboat
leaves without you.

51
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,200
Now don't forget to write!

52
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,160
And be sure to
give our best wishes

53
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:05,080
to our friend Kenshin
when you find him.

54
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,140
Bon voyage!

55
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:07,060
So long!

56
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:08,090
Be safe!

57
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:09,290
And don't forget to write!

58
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:11,160
Come back soon, okay?

59
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:14,030
Goodbye!

60
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:20,260
♪

61
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:22,080
All right, Yoshi,
now our mission

62
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,200
is to go find Kenshin.

63
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,210
That's right.

64
00:03:24,210 --> 00:03:29,190
♪

65
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:33,150
(crash)

66
00:03:35,130 --> 00:03:36,230
Yah!

67
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:45,140
(crash)

68
00:03:45,140 --> 00:04:04,200
♪

69
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,050
I'll get stronger.

70
00:04:06,050 --> 00:04:09,020
So strong that Kenshin will know

71
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:12,170
that I should have
gone along with him.

72
00:04:12,170 --> 00:04:19,160
♪

73
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,180
I'm not your weakness, Kenshin.

74
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:25,200
You'll see.

75
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,280
And I shall prove
it to you in Edo.

76
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,170
You hear me, Kenshin?

77
00:04:29,170 --> 00:04:31,230
In Edo!

78
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:32,150
(sneezes)

79
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:46,280
Strange.

80
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:50,200
I never thought that I
would walk this road again.

81
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,050
Look, Mom, a sword.

82
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:56,220
Sh, be quiet.

83
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,160
He looks like a samurai.

84
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,280
What's with him?

85
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,180
Do you think he doesn't know

86
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:03,220
about the new decree

87
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:05,280
banning the wearing
of swords in public?

88
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:08,040
He looks dangerous to me.

89
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:12,150
The best thing to do
is to stay away from him.

90
00:05:12,150 --> 00:05:13,190
♪

91
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:15,010
Did you say goodbye to that girl

92
00:05:15,010 --> 00:05:18,260
at Kamiya Dojo?

93
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:20,280
Sorry, I shouldn't
have said that.

94
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:22,180
From now on we're
fellow warriors

95
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:24,260
who are going to fight
the Shishio Group together,

96
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:26,160
so let's make the best of it.

97
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,110
Fight together?

98
00:05:27,110 --> 00:05:28,140
Yes.

99
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:30,050
You see, since the
Okubo assassination

100
00:05:30,050 --> 00:05:32,130
the police are facing
some serious problems.

101
00:05:32,130 --> 00:05:35,110
Therefore I was assigned to
handle the situation in Edo.

102
00:05:35,110 --> 00:05:36,230
I get the feeling

103
00:05:36,230 --> 00:05:39,240
you don't like the idea
of joining forces, Kenshin.

104
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,260
Not really.

105
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:42,050
I understand that.

106
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:43,070
But you'll have to anyway,

107
00:05:43,070 --> 00:05:44,060
like it or not.

108
00:05:44,060 --> 00:05:45,140
Come on.

109
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:49,100
If we leave now we can
catch the ship for Osaka.

110
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:51,120
Nope, I'm going to
take the Tokaido Road.

111
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,160
Hm?

112
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,000
The government will
pay for your ticket

113
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,080
so if you're broke just
don't worry about it.

114
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:59,150
It's not about the money.

115
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,270
Shishio is crafty like a fox.

116
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:03,270
If he arranges an attack
while I'm on the ship

117
00:06:03,270 --> 00:06:05,080
there'd be no place to fight

118
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:07,150
where innocent people
wouldn't be put in danger.

119
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:09,180
I can't allow that to happen.

120
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:11,030
You still think like a wanderer

121
00:06:11,030 --> 00:06:12,140
living in a world that exists

122
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:14,050
only in your dreams.

123
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:18,030
Perhaps it's time
for me to wake you up.

124
00:06:18,030 --> 00:06:20,290
I would be glad to fight
you any time you like, Saito.

125
00:06:20,290 --> 00:06:22,260
But I have no intention
of letting anyone

126
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:26,090
who isn't involved
in this get hurt.

127
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:28,150
That's why I'm taking
this journey alone.

128
00:06:28,150 --> 00:06:34,090
♪

129
00:06:34,090 --> 00:06:35,210
Aren't you forgetting something?

130
00:06:35,210 --> 00:06:37,140
Like what?

131
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:40,010
Shishio's spies.

132
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:42,170
He's got a very efficient
information network.

133
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:44,010
And he'll know
exactly where you are

134
00:06:44,010 --> 00:06:45,080
no matter what route you take.

135
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:48,270
♪

136
00:06:48,270 --> 00:06:53,100
Like it or not your battle
with Shishio's already begun.

137
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:55,120
All I have to do is
have a sword at my side

138
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:57,110
and people will
stay away from me.

139
00:06:57,110 --> 00:06:59,220
That way I won't
have to involve anyone.

140
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:02,280
Makoto Shishio was
responsible for Okubo's death.

141
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:04,210
That's why I must go to Edo,

142
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:07,280
to stop Shishio's
reign of terror.

143
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:10,040
I wonder what awaits me
at the end of my journey.

144
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,020
(whistle)

145
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:13,230
Hold it now.

146
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:15,160
You've got some
nerve wearing a sword

147
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:18,260
in front of an officer
of the law, young man.

148
00:07:18,260 --> 00:07:20,050
Stop!

149
00:07:20,050 --> 00:07:23,230
Hold it right
there, you villain!

150
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:24,290
I'm out of here.

151
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:27,220
Stop, stop in the
name of the law!

152
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:33,170
♪

153
00:07:33,170 --> 00:07:36,270
It's so lonely here now
that everyone's gone.

154
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:40,160
I'll take good care of
things while they're away.

155
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,250
Hm, should be locked.

156
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:43,290
It's open.

157
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:45,160
But I have the only key.

158
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:46,280
Unless...

159
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:48,210
Kenshin!

160
00:07:48,210 --> 00:07:51,080
He's come back!

161
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,250
Kenshin?

162
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:57,120
♪

163
00:07:57,120 --> 00:08:02,070
Aoshi, you?

164
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:04,200
I want you to tell
me where Battosai is.

165
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,020
Unbelievable.

166
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:07,210
But we all thought
you were dead.

167
00:08:07,210 --> 00:08:10,210
But after all this time
you must have escaped.

168
00:08:10,210 --> 00:08:12,250
That's right.

169
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:15,050
Even if I knew where he was

170
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:18,230
I would never ever tell you.

171
00:08:18,230 --> 00:08:20,210
You tell me now.

172
00:08:20,210 --> 00:08:21,240
Or die.

173
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:28,180
♪

174
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:31,130
He's on his way to Edo.

175
00:08:31,130 --> 00:08:36,040
♪

176
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:38,020
And just who the hell are you?

177
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:40,170
Goro Fujita, a policeman,

178
00:08:40,170 --> 00:08:42,200
and I'm working undercover.

179
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,260
No, your name's Saito.

180
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:47,200
You're a former head of the
Shinsen Group, third division.

181
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,170
You're an expert at gotatsu.

182
00:08:49,170 --> 00:08:51,160
Now it looks like you're
just a government lackey.

183
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:53,000
I see.

184
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,170
It seems to me your Oni
Gang's information is accurate

185
00:08:55,170 --> 00:08:59,130
as usual.

186
00:08:59,130 --> 00:09:00,180
The reason I came here

187
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:02,100
was because I heard
that another survivor

188
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:05,210
of the end of the Tokugawa
era had come to Tokyo.

189
00:09:05,210 --> 00:09:07,060
I wanted to tell
you what's happened

190
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:09,290
since you secluded
yourself on that mountain.

191
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:16,010
♪

192
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:22,220
Makoto Shishio.

193
00:09:22,220 --> 00:09:25,180
Let's say Battosai
is killed by Shishio.

194
00:09:25,180 --> 00:09:26,290
That he isn't coming back.

195
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:29,090
In that case, tell me,

196
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:31,140
how would you like to go to Edo?

197
00:09:31,140 --> 00:09:33,040
I don't need to.

198
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:38,160
I'm the only one that can do
battle with Battosai and win.

199
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:42,150
You have a great
deal of confidence.

200
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:46,190
The question to me is whether
or not it's overconfidence.

201
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,160
How could you give
him that information?

202
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,150
He wants to kill Kenshin!

203
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:52,100
Now that he knows
where Kenshin is headed

204
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:54,100
he'll know the
routes he might take.

205
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,280
He'll know where to
look, and if he finds--

206
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,250
Look on the bright side.

207
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:57,260
If I hadn't have told him that

208
00:09:57,260 --> 00:10:01,150
he might very well
have killed you.

209
00:10:01,150 --> 00:10:04,020
Aoshi Shinomori became
head of the Oni Gang

210
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:06,080
at the age of 15.

211
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,240
If I can find a way to use him

212
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:12,060
it'll give us a
tremendous advantage.

213
00:10:12,060 --> 00:10:15,230
I like the way your
mind works, policeman.

214
00:10:15,230 --> 00:10:18,030
Yeah, Saito, I agree.

215
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:19,190
Aoshi Shinomori.

216
00:10:19,190 --> 00:10:23,040
Could be quite useful indeed.

217
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:27,120
Would you stop already?

218
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,060
Come back here, you rascal!

219
00:10:29,060 --> 00:10:30,170
You scofflaw!

220
00:10:30,170 --> 00:10:32,150
I'm warning you, don't
get involved with me,

221
00:10:32,150 --> 00:10:35,110
you could get hurt,
leave me alone.

222
00:10:35,110 --> 00:10:38,250
Halt you cad,
halt at once, halt!

223
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:43,220
(crash)

224
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:45,080
Who am I kidding?

225
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,200
This isn't training.

226
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:50,110
It's merely destroying nature.

227
00:10:50,110 --> 00:10:52,130
Where's the road to Edo?

228
00:10:52,130 --> 00:10:56,200
Where is the road to Edo?

229
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:19,210
♪

230
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:22,180
I won't give up until
I destroy Battosai.

231
00:11:22,180 --> 00:11:23,290
Only then can I bring flowers

232
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:28,120
to honor the graves
of my fallen comrades.

233
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:30,110
Give me that bottle of sake.

234
00:11:30,110 --> 00:11:32,110
We gotta meet some girls.

235
00:11:32,110 --> 00:11:34,050
Nah, you're too ugly.

236
00:11:34,050 --> 00:11:37,060
Why, you, I oughtta...

237
00:11:37,060 --> 00:11:38,260
You should talk!

238
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:40,020
Hey, look who's here.

239
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:41,130
Well, it's about time.

240
00:11:41,130 --> 00:11:42,270
We've been waiting for you.

241
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:44,210
You're Aoshi Shinomori, right?

242
00:11:44,210 --> 00:11:47,250
Yeah, he's Aoshi, all right.

243
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,010
Who are you?

244
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:52,100
And why are you here?

245
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:54,000
We're here for you.

246
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,060
We were sent here
by Mr. Shishio.

247
00:11:56,060 --> 00:11:59,050
We're the Four
Giants of Abukuma.

248
00:11:59,050 --> 00:12:00,100
And we're here to tell you

249
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:02,210
that Mr. Shishio
wants to see ya.

250
00:12:02,210 --> 00:12:04,130
He's a great man
and doesn't have time

251
00:12:04,130 --> 00:12:05,240
to just see anyone.

252
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,130
Even we rarely get to see him

253
00:12:07,130 --> 00:12:09,040
and we work for him.

254
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:11,000
Going to meet him
is a great honor.

255
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,090
We better go now.

256
00:12:12,090 --> 00:12:15,290
We don't wanna keep
him waiting, do we?

257
00:12:15,290 --> 00:12:17,130
You can tell Shishio

258
00:12:17,130 --> 00:12:18,230
if he wants to see me

259
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:20,210
he'll have to come to me.

260
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:22,280
And if you dare to desecrate
the graves of my comrades

261
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:24,190
you will all die.

262
00:12:24,190 --> 00:12:25,250
Not only you,

263
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:29,170
but Shishio as well.

264
00:12:29,170 --> 00:12:32,170
Ha, so much for
your dead buddies.

265
00:12:32,170 --> 00:12:34,080
Threatening us
was stupid enough.

266
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:37,190
But threatening Mr.
Shishio was really idiotic.

267
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:39,180
Why do you say that?

268
00:12:39,180 --> 00:12:42,190
(all)
Because now we gotta kill ya.

269
00:12:42,190 --> 00:12:45,120
♪

270
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,140
A long sword.

271
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:49,030
You lost to Battosai
and changed your weapon.

272
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:51,120
It doesn't matter
how good you are.

273
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:55,290
You can't protect yourself
from all of us with one sword.

274
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:57,070
Huh?

275
00:12:57,070 --> 00:12:58,080
